[moddesc {NaviServer Manual}]

[titledesc {NaviServer Configuration Parameter Reference}]

[description]

This manual page provides a reference for NaviServer configuration sections
and parameters.  It is generated from the machine-readable configuration
documentation used by NaviServer tooling, such as the nsstats module, and
therefore focuses on the meaning, type, default value, and status of
individual configuration parameters.

[para]
The reference is organized by configuration scope.  Global sections describe
process-wide settings, per-server sections describe settings below
[const {ns/server/$server}], and module sections describe parameters accepted
by module implementations such as network drivers or server modules.

[para]
This page complements [uri admin-config.html], which explains the structure of
NaviServer configuration files, common configuration patterns, and deployment
examples.  Use [uri admin-config.html] for conceptual guidance and examples,
and this page as a parameter reference.

