[section {Server Module Configuration}]

[para]
Server modules extend a virtual server with additional functionality such as
access logging, CGI execution, control-port access, reverse proxying, or
other application services.  They are usually loaded through
[const {ns/server/$server/modules}] and configured below
[const {ns/server/$server/module/$name}].  The final path component
[const {$name}] is the configured module instance name; the accepted parameters
are determined by the module implementation.

[example_begin]
 ns_section ns/server/$server/modules {
    ns_param nslog  nslog
    ns_param nscgi  nscgi
 }
 
 ns_section ns/server/$server/module/nslog {
    ns_param file access.log
 }
[example_end]

