[section {Database Configuration}]

[para]
Database support is optional. Installations that use NaviServer database
integration load the [const nsdb] module for a virtual server, select the
server's available database pools in [const {ns/server/$server/db}], and define
the global database pool configurations under [const ns/db/pools] and
[const {ns/db/pool/$dbpool}].

[para]
The placeholder [const {$dbpool}] denotes a database pool name defined in
[const ns/db/pools]. Database pools are global and may be shared by multiple
virtual servers.

[para]
Database drivers are external modules for the nsdb interface. They must be
compiled and installed separately, then registered in [const ns/db/drivers]
before database pools can use them. The placeholder [const {$dbdriver}] denotes
a database driver name defined in [const ns/db/drivers].

[para]
For a broader introduction to NaviServer database access and administration,
see [uri admin-db.html {Database Access and Configuration}].

